MESSAGE.value: Component spawning for nscomponents working perfectly

Now with classes!
Station and NSComponent are the first.
Mostly comments. Commented out old code for clarity. Re-assessed goals.

Further incorporated variables and functions as class attributes and methods. Wrote the EWComponent class and its method spawn_ewcorridors(). Need to flesh out EWComponent with nsbranches and then I'll be ready for graphics and equipment!
Finished branches in WEComponents, randomized station orientation and starting ns/we branch probabilities.
Completely set up pygame display and tiles, along with mouse events and scrolling!
Refined display and mouse scrolling and zoom, changed airlocks to spawn at all exterior doors and changed components to keep one tile separation when spawning.
Created and implemented a starry background which is pretty great. Also started implementing flavors and wrote pseudocode for flavored equipment.
"Finished" initial implementation of flavored equipment. Need to debug and expand...
Created and implemented tile patterns! Maybe too much memory though?

Created Tile objects which show what to draw and also store data such as flavor. Changed equipmentFlavors to get defined by the Tile objects and then point back to the Tile objects.
Added NiH2 batteries!

Created station images that equipment and airlocks get blitted onto, starting with a transparent png, and then the stations get blitted onto the screen along with corridors and empty tiles. Maybe I'll put the latter two on the stations as well at some point :P
Made zooming better!
Created more equipment bitmaps!
